The following companies had unusual
price changes in Argentine trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of the close of trading in
Buenos Aires. The  Merval (MERVAL)  Index rose 1 percent to 2,369.22.  Holcim  Argentina  SA (JMIN AF), a cement producer, fell 3.1
percent to 3.10 pesos. Argentinaâ€™s construction activity fell
5.4 percent in May from a year earlier, the national statistics
institute reported June 29.  Natural gas distributors rallied after a report in the
newspaper BAE said Metrogas SA (METR AF) may receive a 100
million-peso ($22 million) loan from Banco de la Nacion.
Argentina fueled speculation other companies in the industry may
also receive  government aid , said Leonardo Bazzi, head of
research at Buenos Aires-based brokerage Puente Hermanos SA.  Transportadora de Gas del Sur SA  (TGSU2 AR) rose 1.8
percent to 2.24 pesos.  Transportadora de Gas del Norte SA  (TGNO4
AF) advanced 2.9 percent to 47 centimos. There was no trading in
Metrogas, which closed at 60 centimos on June 29.  To contact the reporter on this story:
